  "content_hash": "dd6a8f6064fb648c996dce59ef274ae874f1faa618e02b8cc67f1ed6ba489745",
  "dependencies": [],
  "description": "Architecture pattern for assembling a zero-trust posture in Salesforce \u2014 there is no single zero-trust toggle. The pattern composes High-Assurance Sessions, Real-Time Event Monitoring (RTEM) Transaction Security Policies, Login Flows for conditional access, Event Monitoring for continuous verification, Mobile Security for device compliance, and a Permission Set Group strategy that defaults-deny. Covers the gotcha that not all RTEM event types support TSP enforcement (IdentityVerificationEvent and MobileEmailEvent do NOT). NOT for MFA-only rollouts (see security/mfa-enforcement-strategy), NOT for the LLM-side Einstein Trust Layer (different concept), NOT for Apex CRUD/FLS enforcement patterns (see apex/apex-stripinaccessible-and-fls-enforcement).",
  "file_location": "skills/architect/zero-trust-salesforce-patterns",
  "id": "architect/zero-trust-salesforce-patterns",
  "inputs": [
    "Org's current MFA, SSO, and session-management posture",
    "Whether Shield (Event Monitoring + Real-Time Event Monitoring) is licensed",
    "Mobile Security / MDM tooling currently in use, if any",
    "List of high-assurance objects/operations to gate behind step-up auth"
  ],
